Sound-effect assets

The WAV files in assets/sfx/ are generated locally and CC0-derived: procedural
cues are pure DSP synthesis (combat_generators, ui_game_state_generator), and
the two trumpet cues are Strudel pure-synth patterns (music_sound_generator) —
synthesised waveforms only, no sample banks. They carry no standalone-use
restriction and may be freely used, modified, and redistributed. Per-file
provenance is in docs/asset-sources.md and docs/audio-provenance.json.

The terminal font supplied by soft-raster (third_party/soft-raster/src/font8x16.h)
is extracted from Debian
console-setup's Lat15-Fixed16 console font, which Debian declares public
domain ("All console fonts are public domain by nature"). Its X11-lineage
permissive notice is preserved in that dependency's header.
